The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                A seven-year-old child fell off an autorickshaw after the driver suddenly pressed the accelerator in an attempt to overtake another three-wheeler and was crushed under the wheels of a truck in Howrahs Bauria on Sunday afternoon. Police said the child, Ajay Ruidas, was returning home to Uluberia with his mother from a relatives house in Bauria. The truck driver fled after the mishap. Residents blocked the road around 2pm demanding immediate arrest of the driver. The blockade was lifted after an hour when police promised action.     Sitalprasad and Mita Halder, a couple in their 50s, were arrested in Lake Town on Sunday on the charge of abetting the suicide of their 21-year-old domestic help, Gargi Rao. Police said Gargi was found hanging from a ceiling fan in the Halders apartment on November 16. An unnatural death case was registered but a probe revealed that the couple used to torture the help. The couple were picked up following a complaint by neighbours.     Multi-ride Metro Railway tickets were sold from ticket counters at the stations from 7am to 1pm on Sunday. Multi-ride tickets will be sold next Sunday too at the same time.    One person was arrested after a gang war broke out in Watgunge on Sunday morning. Aiyaz Ahmed, alias Anil, was arrested from in front of 16 Dent Mission Road where the clash broke out.     Thieves decamped with gold and silver jewellery worth Rs 1 lakh from a Shiva temple on Belur Dharmatala Road, under Bally police station, early on Sunday. Police said a resident saw the lock of the temples grille gate broken and alerted them. A probe was started on the basis of a complaint lodged by the temple authorities.    The body of 35-year-old Ajmeera Bibi was found at Central Park in Pailan on Sunday morning with her severed head lying in a bush 100m away. Ajmeera, a resident of Raspunja near Thakurpukur, was missing for a year and a half. Her husband, too, has been missing.                                                                                                                                                  
